Regarding the value preset: Did you manually set the values on those fields with some custom script? If so, then yes they get cleaned up again because as far as i've learned it, the form is a react application that gets initialised once the code snippet of HubSpot is on your page and running so you have to update the internal state in react. Therefore it's a bit tricky to manually set values for it with custom scripting - but it's possible:
```
inputElement.value = value;
inputElement.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('change'));
inputElement.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('input'));
inputElement.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('blur'));
```
where inputElement is your input that you targeted via `document.querySelector`

